opicID=10.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.maxho.com/~shader/eq/resh_icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard epic quest.</span><hr size=1> more info from graffe.com<br><br><br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm5.showMessage?topicID=504.topic">pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffe...=504.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><br><br>The note we take to Camin has four items on it -<br><br>'Dragon bones - Plane of Fear' : Suspected to be found on Dragoliche. <br>'Jet Black egg' - Unknown' : No ideas as of yet. <br>Mistletoe powder - Old Sebilis' : Found on Tolapmulj. LORE ITEM - NO DROP. <br>'Rune of Lost Thought - Unknown' : No ideas as of yet. <br>Camin can be found at the Vasty Deep Inn within Erudin. To find him inside the Inn, open the front door to the Inn and go up the stairs on your right. Follow the hallway around the second floor and Camin is found behind the first door upon your left. Off the bat, he is normally indifferent or apprehensive to everyone. To raise faction, hand him the note that was given to you by Soloman and you will receive the following faction adjustments:<br><br>TrueSpirit (positive faction) <br>Camin will now reply with -<br><br>Camin says, 'So you have met Solomen, eh? He is a man with a wealth of knowledge. It is good to hear he is well.<br><br>Now hail Camin and he will respond with this -<br><br>Camin says 'Go away! I have no time for you! <br><br>If this happens, you need to raise your faction to warmly with him. The easiest way to do so is the following: <br><br>Go back to Solusek Ro and bind yourself at Solomen. <br>you say 'I agree.' Solomen will hand you the note to take back to Camin. <br>Gate to Tox and run to Erudin. <br>Hand Camin the note and get positive faction with TrueSpirit. <br>Do this until you are warmly with Camin. (approx. 20 times) <br>Once you are warmly with Camin: <br><br>you say, 'What are you searching for?'<br>Camin says 'Ah! A smart one, I see! If you really wish to know about such a thing, you will have to help me finance my studies. The knowledge I have acquired and researched did not come cheaply.<br><br>At this point, hand Camin 1000 platinum pieces. Doing this will make Camin reply with:<br><br>Camin says, 'Good, good, you show a willingness to learn of this with your offer. What I can tell you is that Solusek Ro had four followers who had shown exceptional aptitude in the arts of wizardry. Solusek Ro himself tutored them. He considered them to be like his own children. I know of one who still exists. He goes by the name of Arantir Karondor. He used to specialize in the storing of magic into physical objects. Arantir has been hiding for many, many years and will most assuredly be going by another name, so keep your eyes open. Anyway, be off, I need to continue my research. Return to me if you ever find Arantir Karondor.'<br><br>Now to find Arantir Karondor. I honestly have no idea what Verant was thinking when they did this part of the quest. There are zero clues as to who or where this person is and honestly, it's sort of disturbing to me that every other class' quest is straightforward, but still has a very good degree of difficulty. None the less, there is a female NPC vendor in Halas named 'Dargon' that sells a potion called Ro's Breath (8 Charges of Shield of Lava, MAGIC, LORE, NO DROP). She is located in front of the Shaman guild. Purchase this potion from Dargon (evil races be warned - you ARE KOS!) for the sum of about 900pp to 1100pp depending on your faction and charisma.<br><br>Now take this potion back to Camin in Erudin and hand it to him. He will reply with the following:<br><br>Camin says 'Very interesting... I've seen this work before. Yes, yes! It's the work of Arantir Karondor! Give this back to the person you got it from. Maybe he will have a clue to Arantir's location.' <br><br>Camin gives you back the potion and you must take it back to Dargon in Halas.<br>Note: you cannot skip the previous trip to Camin. You absolutely, must hand the potion to Camin. If you try to skip the trip to Erudin, you will get the following message from Dargon: &quot;I didnt request this item, but thank you very much&quot;.<br><br>Back in Halas, hand the Ro's Breath potion back to Dargon. She will turn into blue robe adorned, Arantir Karondor and reply with:<br><br>Dargon says 'So, I've been discovered! You must know Camin - he is one of the only people who could have recognized my work. I have worked very hard to mask my presence here.' <br><br>You say, 'hail Arantir Karondor' <br>Arantir Karondor says 'Before I tell you anything, I require you to help me. Seek a woman named Challice. Give her this letter and then return to me.'<br><br>The letter that Arantir hands you is actually a ring. Identifying it reveals: &quot;Item Lore: My love has no bounds.&quot; Challice is found in the basement of the Felwithe paladin guild. Hand Challice the ring and she will reply with:<br><br>Challice says 'Oh yes? Arantir? What a fool he was! the man gave me everything, but for all his intelligence, he could never understand why I was truly with him. It was for his power; he could do anything. But when he mysteriously lost it, he became just another toy. I never loved him. Return this ring to him. He will understand that I have no desire to see him again.' <br><br>This new ring, when indentified reads: &quot;Item Lore: I never could love a man like you.&quot; Take this ring back to Arantir and hand it over (you can hand it to either Dargon or Arantir). Then you must hail him to get his attention and go through the following dialogue:<br><br>you say, 'Hail Arantir Karondor!'<br>Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, but it pains my heart to see this. How I could love a women like that is beyond me. And yet, I still do love her. It was on the day I was to ask her to marry me that I lost my powers. When I was about to cast my greatest spell to prove my love to her, my magic failed. She ran out on me that day. But enough of me, do you wish to hear my story?' <br><br>you say, 'I wish to hear your story.'<br>Arantir Karondor says 'I once was one of four true followers of Solusek Ro. So great were the four of us that Solusek Ro himself made us each a special item. We did not know what the others' items were, but we realized that was for our own safety. Each one of us, after receiving the item, began to plot against Solusek Ro. Each of us believed we had enough power to dominate Norrath. Solusek Ro saw this and at the time we needed our powers most, he stripped us of them. Now I know two of the other wizards by name. One was called Sylen Tyrn, the other's name was Demunir Scry. The last wizard was a gnome, but I can't think of his name.<br><br>you say, 'What about Sylen Tyrn?'<br>Arantir Karondor says 'Sylen was a high elf wizard, and like many high elves, he believed himself to be better than others. Because of his birth, he thought he was more noble and more intelligent than anyone else. I heard how met his demise - while flying over a vast area of water, his powers were stripped from him in midflight. He fell and was captured by a rival wizard who specialized in magics of the water. Search for that wizard and you could find a trace of Sylen.<br><br>More than likely, the 'trace' of Sylen Tyrn is found off of Phiningel Autropos deep in Kedge Keep - the Blue Crystal Staff. When this item is identified, the power of Solusek Ro radiates from within.<br><br>you say, 'What about Demunir Scry?'<br>Arantir Karondor says 'Demunir was a human in a rush for power. He was extremely intelligent and resourceful but, unfortunately, was more interested in destructive magic. Hearing of an ancient land, he immediately traveled to it, believing there to be powerful relics left undiscovered there. While exploring, he came upon a dwelling that housed a powerful warrior. Believing himself to be more powerful, he attempted to take this dwelling for himself. While in battle with this warrior, Solusek Ro stole his powers and left him helpless. It is said that Demunir's item is the warrior's most prized trophy.<br><br>The Demunir item is thought to either be the Gnarled Staff off of Venril Sathir from within Karnor's Castle or a warrior item found from deep within The Hole.<br><br>you say, 'What about the gnome?'<br>Arantir Karondor says 'Ah, the gnome I know very little about. I know he was small and crafty, and that he had a brother. His brother's craft was that of making fireworks, and he was the unfortunate victim of one of his own experiments. His firework exploded, leaving his mind diminished in capacity, even for a gnome. I remember others calling him 'Old Stewpot' in jest. I do not know if this is his birth name, but it may help you to locate him. I hear he also stays close to water because of the explosion. You never know when another gnomish invention will go awry. Give him this letter to help motivate him to remember. <br><br>The gnome seems to be Kandin Firepot. Kandin can be found in the Southwest region of ButcherBlock Mountains (-1500 +2800) near the ocean. Handing Kandin the note from Arantir results in the following:<br><br>Kandin Firepot says 'Brother! I have one of those. He's great, but he's dead. His name was Gabstik and he was a really powerful wizard. I still have one of his greatest possessions! Hey, I know! You can help me with my greatest firework! I need you to get me a skin to put the powder from my firework in. That's the only thing I can think of to use though I cannot get myself. I need a skin that is dry and brittle, yet can still be shaped. So go fetch me some and I'll scratch your back.<br><br><br>Thats as far as anyone has got. Hope this helps.  <p><b><img src="http://www.maxho.com/~shader/eq/resh_dragon.jpg" border=0 vspace=10 hspace=10><br><font face="Verdana" color="#000022" size=2>Reshion Seora, <a href="http://www.prexus.com/Legions">Legions</a> of Prexus<br>Wizard of 52nd season and growing<br></font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usileena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sileena</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/00 8:44:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard epic quest.</span><hr size=1> Anyone seen Mr. Firepot as of late in BB...I headed over there and no gnome...have a new idea for a skin I want to try...<br><br>Sil --- out! <p><b><font color=#000099>Sileena Firestarter</font></b><br><b><font color=#3399EE>Master of the Dreaded Ice Comet</font></b><br><b><font color=#990000>49th level Wizard</font></b><br><br><b><font color=#000099>Tinee Shrimp</font></b><br><b><font color=#3399EE>Shortest drunk warrior in Norrath</font></b><br><b><font color=#990000>8th level Warrior</font></b><br><br><b><i><font color=#00DD88>This is your brain = [--]</font></b></i><br><b><i><font color=#00DD88>This is your brain on Everquest= [-LOADING..Please wait-]</font></b></i><br><b><i><font color=#00DD88>Any Difference?</font></b></i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uunizen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Unizen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/00 3:21:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm12